### Window and Application Management (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/e2b-dev/e2b/blob/main/apps/web/src/app/(docs)/docs/sdk-reference/desktop-js-sdk/v2.0.1/sandbox/page.mdx

Provides functionalities to interact with application windows and launch applications within the sandbox. Methods include getting window IDs by application name, retrieving the current window ID, getting window titles by ID, launching applications with optional URIs, and opening files or URLs in their default applications. All operations return Promises.

```typescript
/**
 * Get the window ID of the window with the given title.
 * @param application The name or title of the application window.
 * @returns A Promise that resolves with an array of window IDs matching the application.
 */
getApplicationWindows(application: string): Promise<string[]>;

/**
 * Get the current window ID.
 * @returns A Promise that resolves with the ID of the currently active window.
 */
getCurrentWindowId(): Promise<string>;

/**
 * Get the title of the window with the given ID.
 * @param windowId The ID of the window.
 * @returns A Promise that resolves with the title of the specified window.
 */
getWindowTitle(windowId: string): Promise<string>;

/**
 * Launch an application.
 * @param application The name of the application to launch.
 * @param uri An optional URI to open within the application.
 * @returns A Promise that resolves when the application is launched.
 */
launch(application: string, uri?: string): Promise<void>;

/**
 * Open a file or a URL in the default application.
 * @param fileOrUrl The path to the file or the URL to open.
 * @returns A Promise that resolves when the file or URL is opened.
 */
open(fileOrUrl: string): Promise<void>;
```

